Constable -- Justice of the Peace Ward 4
Chief of Police -- Village of Montpelier
Sub. Rd. Dist. #1 of Rd. Dist. #2 -- 5 Mills - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Sub-Road District Number One of Road District Number Two Proposition
(Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall Sub-Road District Number One of Road District Number Two of St. Helena Parish, Louisiana (the "District"), be authorized to levy a special tax of five (5) mills on all property subject to taxation within the District (an estimated $27,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2025, for the purpose of maintaining and keeping in repair the public roads, highways and bridges in the District?

Race.SpecificTitle: 5th Wd. Recreation Dist. -- 15 Mills - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Fifth Ward Recreation District Proposition
(Millage Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall Fifth Ward Recreation District of the Parish of St. Helena, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a special tax of fifteen (15) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $88,875 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2015 and ending with the year 2024, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining, operating and/or supporting recreational parks, playgrounds, facilities, equipment and programs for the District?
